                <article class="article">
                    <h1 class="primary-heading js-dynamic-gradient">65 Fellows Elected into the American Academy of Microbiology</h1>

                        <p class="meta">
                            Feb. 16, 2021<br />

                        </p>

                    <strong>Washington, DC &ndash; February 16, 2021 &ndash;&nbsp;</strong>In February, <a href="https://asm.org/Academy/Academy">the&nbsp;American Academy of Microbiology&nbsp;(Academy)</a> elected 65 new Fellows to the Class of 2021. Fellows of the American Academy of Microbiology, an honorific leadership group within the ASM, are elected annually through a highly selective, peer-review process, based on their records of scientific achievement and original contributions that have advanced microbiology.&nbsp;The Academy received&nbsp;150&nbsp;nominations this year and&nbsp;elected 65 into the 2021 Fellowship Class.&nbsp;<br />
<br />
There are over 2,500 Fellows in the Academy representing all subspecialties of the microbial sciences and involved in basic and applied research, teaching, public health, industry, and government service.&nbsp;In addition, Fellows hail from all around the globe. The Class of&nbsp;2021 is a diverse class and represents Fellows from&nbsp;11 different countries, including&nbsp;Australia, Canada, China (Mainland), France, Ireland, Sweden, Slovenia, Mexico, and Singapore, the U.K. and the U.S.<br />
<br />
The 2021 Academy Fellows are:<br />
<br />
&middot; <b>Alex Andrianopoulos</b>, Ph.D., University of Melbourne<br />
<br />
&middot; <b>Robert Arkowitz</b>, Ph.D., Institute of Biology Valrose, Université Côte d&rsquo;Azur<br />
<br />
&middot; <b>Esther Babady</b>, Ph.D., D(ABMM), FIDSA, Memorial Sloan Kettering Cancer Center<br />
<br />
&middot; <b>Frédéric Barras</b>, Ph.D., Pasteur Institute<br />
<br />
&middot; <b>Seth Bordenstein</b>, Ph.D., Vanderbilt University<br />
<br />
&middot; <b>Tanja Bosak</b>, Ph.D., Massachusetts Institute of Technology<br />
<br />
&middot; <b>Samuel Brown</b>, Ph.D., Georgia Institute of Technology<br />
<br />
&middot; <b>Lynn Bry</b>, M.D., Ph.D., Harvard Medical School, Brigham &amp; Women&#39;s Hospital<br />
<br />
&middot; <b>Daniel Buckley</b>, Ph.D., Cornell University<br />
<br />
&middot; <b>Geraldine Butler</b>, Ph.D., University College Dublin<br />
